{"nodes": [{"id": "domain", "label": "Ubiquitous Language (DOMAIN.md)", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "DOMAIN.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Shared contract: Python, Rust, Go mirror the exact same names and boundaries so a feature always has the same home in every language. Compression is target-size driven."}, {"id": "domain_shared_kernel", "label": "Shared Kernel", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DOMAIN.md", "source_location": "\u00a7Shared Kernel", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Immutable value objects used by all contexts; W2 moves (ImageKind, ResampleFilter, CompressionTarget, TargetSizeSearch, LosslessOutcome, constants) ended the image<->pdf bidirectional coupling flagged in docs/REVIEW.md."}, {"id": "domain_bytebudget", "label": "ByteBudget", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DOMAIN.md", "source_location": "\u00a7Shared Kernel", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "domain_qualityfloor", "label": "QualityFloor", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DOMAIN.md", "source_location": "\u00a7Shared Kernel", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "A domain invariant \u2014 an adapter may not return a result below it. SSIM 0.90 shown decorative (RESEARCH \u00a73); target is SSIMULACRA2 >= 70 portal / 80 archival; single enforcement point lands in W5."}, {"id": "domain_targetsizesearch", "label": "TargetSizeSearch", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DOMAIN.md", "source_location": "\u00a7pdf Context / domain services", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Binary search over encoder quality (monotone size<->quality predicate), then dimensions if the floor conflicts with budget. One algorithm home \u2014 photo byte ceilings reuse it rather than reimplementing."}, {"id": "domain_budgetdecomposition", "label": "BudgetDecomposition", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DOMAIN.md", "source_location": "\u00a7pdf Context / domain services", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Allocate a PDF's byte budget across images proportional to rendered area \u2014 spend bytes where eyes go; reserve non-image bytes measured after the structural pass."}, {"id": "domain_effectivedpi", "label": "EffectiveDpi", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DOMAIN.md", "source_location": "\u00a7Shared Kernel", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Computed from page geometry (CTM), never image metadata \u2014 scanners often omit or lie. Hard rule #3."}, {"id": "domain_compressiontarget", "label": "CompressionTarget", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DOMAIN.md", "source_location": "\u00a7pdf Context / domain", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "domain_photospec", "label": "PhotoSpec Presets", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DOMAIN.md", "source_location": "\u00a7photo Context", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Compliance specs are data presets, never code branches \u2014 a new country is a new row. Presets: us_passport, india_passport, india_oci; W7 adds min_bytes and head-rule fields as data."}, {"id": "domain_india_oci", "label": "india_oci Preset (<=200 KB)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DOMAIN.md", "source_location": "\u00a7photo Context", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "domain_sheetlayoutservice", "label": "SheetLayoutService", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DOMAIN.md", "source_location": "\u00a7photo Context / domain services", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Pure tiling math: integer capacity floor(usable/cell), slack distributed as n+1 equal gaps that become cut lanes; 2x2 inch on 4x6 at 300 DPI gives 6-up matching commercial strips."}, {"id": "domain_losslessoptimizer", "label": "LosslessOptimizer Port", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DOMAIN.md", "source_location": "\u00a7image Context / Lossless", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Pixels must be bit-exact: JPEG is entropy-coding-only (mozjpeg, DCT coefficients untouched); PNG recompress. Hard rule #1 (never larger) applies."}, {"id": "domain_qualitymeter", "label": "QualityMeter Port", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DOMAIN.md", "source_location": "\u00a7image Context / Ports", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "domain_imagecodec", "label": "ImageCodec Port", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DOMAIN.md", "source_location": "\u00a7image Context / Ports", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "domain_target_size_algorithm", "label": "Target-Size Compression Algorithm", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "DOMAIN.md", "source_location": "\u00a7Target-Size Algorithm", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Shared across languages: structural lossless pass, CTM census, budget allocation proportional to rendered area, per-image branch by ImageKind (bitonal -> CCITT G4; contone -> DPI cap + quality binary search), retry with lowered dpi_cap, Ghostscript escalation only on BudgetMissed."}, {"id": "domain_hard_rules", "label": "Hard Rules (tests, not suggestions)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "DOMAIN.md", "source_location": "\u00a7Hard Rules", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Six rules encoded as tests in every language: never emit larger output; bitonal via gray-downsample+Otsu+CCITT G4 (never NN, never JPEG); effective DPI from CTM; quality floor is a domain invariant; every adapter behind a port with AGPL deps isolated; frozen-dataclass type discipline mirrored as Go interfaces and Rust traits."}, {"id": "domain_pikepdf_engine", "label": "pikepdf Composite Engine (default)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DOMAIN.md", "source_location": "\u00a7Engines", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Default because the hosted-UI roadmap makes AGPL section 13 network copyleft a real obligation: pikepdf+pypdfium2+Pillow serve with no source-disclosure requirement and measured higher SSIM than both AGPL engines. Surgical image-XObject rewrite; pypdfium2 is only the renderer for SSIM."}, {"id": "domain_pymupdf_engine", "label": "pymupdf+pillow Engine (AGPL)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DOMAIN.md", "source_location": "\u00a7Engines", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Smallest files but AGPL \u2014 avoid for network-served use (section 13); slight generational loss."}, {"id": "domain_ghostscript_engine", "label": "Ghostscript Escalation Engine", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "DOMAIN.md", "source_location": "\u00a7Engines", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Escalation only, fires on BudgetMissed; AGPL, quarantined; slowest with no size/quality edge (ANALYSIS verdict)."}], "edges": [{"source": "domain", "target": "docs_review", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "DOMAIN.md", "source_location": "\u00a7Shared Kernel", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "domain", "target": "docs_research", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "DOMAIN.md", "source_location": "QualityFloor row", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "domain", "target": "docs_plan", "rel